St. George, Staten Island, showing the waterfront as seen from the St. George branch of the New York Public Library, 14 Bay Street. The group of buildings on the extreme right, behind the stone wall, is the United States Lighthouse Station; the ramp running down to the shore leads to the St. George-Brooklyn ferry landing; on the left are the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad yards and a portion of the Richmond Borough Hall. Moving down the Upper New York Bay, in view 1, is the S. S. Acquitania; moving up the bay, in view 2, is the S. S. Leviathan.

P. L. Sperr

View 1: May 2, 1928
View 2: 1928
